data.title: Leslie Vincent Presents Will You Still Love Me Tomorrow: An Evening of Amy Winehouse & Carole King
data.meta_description:
All are welcome!

Brimming with heartache and joy, this show celebrates the resilience  of the human heart and the universal truths that Amy Winehouse  and Carole King’s music both share. Featuring the extraordinary  vocals of Leslie Vincent, along with Ted Godbout on keys, Matt McIntyre on bass, Ben Ehrlich on drums, and Mitch Van Laar on trumpet, this show has  been performed to sold-out crowds in St. Paul and continues to resonate with audience members of all ages. “If you've seen or heard Leslie, you know what an incredible and unique voice she has” — Cherry and Spoon.

6:00 PM Open for drinks and small plates

7:30 PM Concert in the Lounge

Dining

Spanish Omelet and Tomato Chutney

Chorizo and Goat Cheese Stuffed Figs

Spicy Garlic Shrimp

Braised Octopus with Roasted Garlic  Aioli., Orange Segment, and Crispy Garlic 

Crostini with Red Wine Braised Tomato, Feta, Olive Oil and Fresh Oregeno

Please make your reservation for dining through our Front Desk at frontdesk@womansclub.org or 612.813.5300
